oai_dc:dc.dc:title: PORE PRESSURE INDUCED BY WIND WAVES IN SAND BED
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Massel, S.R.
Kaczmarek, L.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: wind waves
pore pressure
sand bed
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The two projects (LUBIATOWO 79 and LUBIATOWO 86) were aimed at study pore pressure behaviour in natural sand bed in the coastal zone of the Baltic sea under the action of storm waves. During both projects, the wave induced pore pressures at the various levels in the sea bed were measured. The collected data were used to verify the applicability of the various theoretical approaches. In the conclusion, the range of the application of the particular analytical method is given.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 21 (1988): Proceedings of 21st Conference on Coastal Engineering, Torremolinos, Spain, 1988.; 75
